    {
      "id": "T18",
      "desc": "translate Japanese",
      "called_tool": null,
      "called_tools": [],
      "expected_tool": "translate",
      "expected_tools": null,
      "tool_correct": false,
      "params_correct": false,
      "params_detail": {},
      "score": 0.0,
      "raw_content": "There are several ways to say \"goodbye\" in Japanese, depending on who you are talking to and whether you are leaving or the other person is leaving.\n\n### 1. The most common ways\n*   **Say\u014dnara (\u3055\u3088\u3046\u306a\u3089):** This is the standard \"goodbye\" you learn in textbooks. However, in daily life, it can sound final\u2014like you won't see the person for a long time (similar to \"farewell\").\n*   **Ja, mata (\u3058\u3083\u3001\u307e\u305f):** This is very common in casual conversation. It means \"See you later\" or \"See you soon.\"\n\n### 2. When you are leaving\nIf you are the one leaving and the other person is staying, you use a phrase that means \"I'm heading out\":\n*   **Osaki ni shitsurei shimasu (\u304a\u5148\u306b\u5931\u793c\u3057\u307e\u3059):** Formal \u2014 used in a business setting when leaving the office before others.\n*   **Nukete ikimasu (\u629c\u3051\u3066\u3044\u304d\u307e\u3059):** Casual \u2014 \"I'm heading out now.\"\n\n### 3. When the other person is leaving\nIf the other person is the one leaving, you use a phrase that means \"safe travels\":\n*   **Ki o tsukete (\u6c17\u3092\u3064\u3051\u3066):** Casual \u2014 \"Take care\" or \"Be careful.\"\n*   **Ki o tsukete kaeraremasen ka (\u6c17\u3092\u3064\u3051\u3066\u5e30\u308c\u307e\u3059\u304b):** Formal \u2014 \"Please get home safely.\"\n\n### 4. Time-specific goodbyes\nInstead of a general \"goodbye,\" Japanese people often use a phrase based on when they will see each other next:\n*   **Mata ashita (\u307e\u305f\u660e\u65e5):** See you tomorrow.\n*   **Mata raish\u016b (\u307e\u305f\u6765\u9031):** See you next week.\n*   **Mata raish\u016b-matsu (\u307e\u305f\u6765\u9031\u672b):** See you next weekend.\n*   **Mata ne (\u307e\u305f\u306d):** A friendly \"See ya!\"\n\n### Summary table\n| Situation | Japanese | Romaji | Meaning |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Standard | \u3055\u3088\u3046\u306a\u3089 | Say\u014dnara | Goodbye |\n| Casual | \u3058\u3083\u3001\u307e\u305f | Ja, mata | See you later |\n| Formal (leaving) | \u304a\u5148\u306b\u5931\u793c\u3057\u307e\u3059 | Osaki ni shitsurei",
      "latency_s": 11.56
